</h3><p class="sc-iLLNPL dGtRC pf-27_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">According to the Health and Safety Executive (HSE), there were approximately 693,000 non-fatal injuries at work reported by employers in 2019/20. Immediate access to first aid can significantly increase the chances of survival and reduce the severity of injuries in emergencies.<br><br>Research indicates that businesses with well-implemented first aid provisions experience higher employee morale and productivity.
